The PC Production function plans, executes, and monitors manufacturing, and also plans, designs, constructs, and maintains manufacturing facilities.

The PC Procurement function selects suppliers and negotiates contracts with them. The function also forecasts demand for raw materials, orders, them, and manages inventory levels, relying heavily on information form the Sales and Production functions.
The Logistics function transports and stores both raw materials and finished goods.
The PC Sales function forecasts sales, takes consolidated orders from DCs, and shares them with the Manufacturing and Logistics functions.
